      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S represents a pinnacle of the 996.2 era, featuring the coveted wide-body architecture and the high-performance braking system derived from the 911 Turbo. The 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine is in peak mechanical health, with a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a clean borescope report confirming no cylinder bore scoring. Power is delivered through a precise 6-speed manual gearbox and a viscous-coupling all-wheel-drive system, providing exceptional traction and composure. The suspension retains factory-fresh damping characteristics, and the undercarriage is free of oxidation. Inside, the cabin is immaculate, showing no bolster wear or UV degradation on the leather surfaces. This is an investment-grade example for a collector who values mechanical integrity and surgical road manners.",
